      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span clinically relevant range of loading rates and fixation torques; at minimum two distinct test configurations evaluated.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted at a single quasi-static loading rate (5 mm/min) and single fixation torque (5 Nm) per ASTM F1717. While this is the standard clinical surrogate condition, only one test configuration was evaluated. Achieved level 2 is below the required level 3; this is a known gap acknowledged in the COU description."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
